cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.HC, cs.NE 

The paper deals with video quality assessment, which involves multimedia data and visual information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves analyzing video quality for spatially or temporally distorted video sequences, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The metric developed in the paper involves analyzing the quality degradation, which can be related to information theory (cs.IT). As the ultimate users are human subjects, the paper also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves simulating the metric to be closer to the developed human visual system, which can be related to neural networks (cs.NE).
